    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen a terminal sends a wheel button event, neovim scrolls by 3 lines. As far as I can tell, this is a hardcoded value. Some terminals (foot, ghostty) pre-multiply wheel clicks for input that was from a discrete wheel click, while sending singular wheel clicks for more precise input methods (ie a touchpad). For these terminals, scrolling behavior can be vastly improved by being able to tell neovim to only scroll 1 line per click.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nA configuration value to change this multiplier. The default can stay at 3.\n\n`vim.opt.scroll_multiplier = 1`",
